{"hash":"33e57ce81afb31a16d831bc6e0e40776dd057607","data":{"markdownPage":{"id":"3bfa0c4518514327b20eddfcb55f2667","title":"@bridge/fs","description":"","path":"/plugin-docs/modules/fs/","timeToRead":1,"content":"<h1 id=\"bridgefs\"><a href=\"#bridgefs\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>@bridge/fs</h1>\n<p>Module that allows plugins to interact with the user's file system.</p>\n<h2 id=\"node-fs-module\"><a href=\"#node-fs-module\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Node FS Module</h2>\n<p>This module exposes all functions Node's <code>fs.promises</code> module provides. You can read its documentation <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v10.x/docs/api/fs.html#fs_fs_promises_api\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"additional-functions\"><a href=\"#additional-functions\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Additional Functions</h2>\n<h3 id=\"writing-json\"><a href=\"#writing-json\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Writing JSON</h3>\n<p><strong>Function Signature:</strong> <code>writeJSON(filePath: string, data: any, beautify = false, fileVersion?: number): Promise&#x3C;void></code></p>\n<p>Write a JavaScript object to a file.</p>\n<h3 id=\"reading-json\"><a href=\"#reading-json\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Reading JSON</h3>\n<p><strong>Function Signature:</strong> <code>readJSON(filePath: string): Promise&#x3C;any></code></p>\n<p>Read a file as JSON and return the equivalent JavaScript object.</p>\n","sidebar":"plugins","next":"","prev":"","author":null,"headings":[{"depth":1,"value":"@bridge/fs","anchor":"#bridgefs"},{"depth":2,"value":"Node FS Module","anchor":"#node-fs-module"},{"depth":2,"value":"Additional Functions","anchor":"#additional-functions"},{"depth":3,"value":"Writing JSON","anchor":"#writing-json"},{"depth":3,"value":"Reading JSON","anchor":"#reading-json"}],"fileI